
- Create a Google Cloud Project

- Create a Google Container Engine Cluster

- Create buckets

    $PROJECT-user
    $PROJECT-directory
    $PROJECT-store
    $PROJECT-letsencrypt

- Create service account for accessing letsencrypt bucket

- Create signed URLs for accessing letsencrypt credentials
  and store them in the global compute metadata

    gsutil signurl -m PUT -d 3650d <path-to-pubkey> gs://$PROJECT-letsencrypt/$SERVICE.cache
    gsutil signurl -m GET -d 3650d <path-to-pubkey> gs://$PROJECT-letsencrypt/$SERVICE.cache
